<emphasis bold="true" box="[563,630,1750,1775]" pageId="4" pageNumber="175">(Q–R)</emphasis>
LMA-00028, paratype A-8, C, right and dorsal views.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="175" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1820,2027]" pageId="4" pageNumber="175">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,347,1820,1846]" pageId="4" pageNumber="175">Description:</emphasis>
Carapace small, suboval in lateral view; ellipsoid in dorsal view. Ventral margin straight; dorsal margin slightly concave, steep posteriorly. Anterior margin broadly rounded; posterior margin infracurvate (sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Luttig, G." box="[151,288,1893,1920]" pageId="4" pageNumber="175" pagination="154 - 184" refId="ref5066" refString="Luttig, G. (1962) Zoologische und palaontologische Ostracoden-Systematik. Palaontologische Zeitschrift, 36, 154 - 184. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / BF 02987899" type="journal article" year="1962">Lüttig 1962</bibRefCitation>
). Greater length at mid-height, greater height and greater width in the median region. LV larger than RV, overlapping along anterodorsal, anterior and almost all the ventral margins, except for the anteroventral portion. Carapace smooth. Sexual dimorphism and internal characters not observed. The instars A-2 to A-7 have a more triangular lateral outline and from A-1 to A-8 a symmetrical dorsal view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="176" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,150,752]" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,150,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida-Lima &amp; Piovesan &amp; Sayão &amp; Lima, 2020" authorityName="Almeida-Lima &amp; Piovesan &amp; Sayão &amp; Lima" authorityYear="2020" box="[324,594,151,176]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Pattersoncypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minima" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[324,594,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">Pattersoncypris minima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[602,693,150,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[602,693,150,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from other species of the genus mainly in the size, by being significantly smaller. This new species was proposed based on the occurrence of complete ontogenetic series, which supports the hypothesis that it is a new taxon instead of an instar of a previously described species. Moreover, morphological differences are noticed when 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida-Lima &amp; Piovesan &amp; Sayão &amp; Lima, 2020" authorityName="Almeida-Lima &amp; Piovesan &amp; Sayão &amp; Lima" authorityYear="2020" box="[644,755,259,284]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Pattersoncypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minima" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[644,755,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">P. minima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[760,849,258,284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[760,849,258,284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is compared to other species of the genus. Compared to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Do Carmo et al., 2013)" baseAuthorityName="Do Carmo" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[181,573,294,321]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Pattersoncypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crepata">
<emphasis box="[181,294,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">P. crepata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Do Carmo, D. A. &amp; Coimbra, J. C. &amp; Whatley, R. C. &amp; Antonietto, L. S. &amp; Citon, R. T. P." box="[309,565,294,321]" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" pagination="91 - 104" refId="ref4300" refString="Do Carmo, D. A., Coimbra, J. C., Whatley, R. C., Antonietto, L. S. &amp; Citon, R. T. P. (2013) Taxonomy of limnic Ostracoda (Crustacea) from the Alagamar Formation, middle-upper Aptian, Potiguar Basin, Northeastern Brazil. Journal of Paleontology, 87, 91 - 104. https: // doi. org / 10.1666 / 11 - 108 R. 1" type="journal article" year="2013">
Do Carmo 
<emphasis box="[436,486,294,320]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">et al</emphasis>
., 2013
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from the Aptian-Albian of Araripe and Potiguar basins, 
<collectingCountry box="[1210,1281,294,320]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, the new species is distinguished by the absence of the prominent hump, the less rounded posterior margin and the positions of greatest height and width. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Antonietto et al., 2012)" baseAuthorityName="Antonietto" baseAuthorityYear="2012" box="[451,805,366,393]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Pattersoncypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alta">
<emphasis box="[451,523,366,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">P. alta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Antonietto, L. S. &amp; Gobbo, S. R. &amp; Do Carmo, D. A. &amp; Assine, M. L. &amp; Fernandes, M. A. M. C. C. &amp; Lima, J. E." box="[538,798,366,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" pagination="659 - 668" refId="ref3548" refString="Antonietto, L. S., Gobbo, S. R., Do Carmo, D. A., Assine, M. L., Fernandes, M. A. M. C. C. &amp; Lima, J. E. (2012) Taxonomy, ontogeny and paleoecology of two species of Harbinia Tsao, 1959 (Crustacea, Ostracoda) from the Santana Formation, Lower Cretaceous, Northeastern Brazil. Journal of Paleontology, 86, 659 - 668. https: // doi. org / 10.1666 / 11 - 012 R. 1" type="journal article" year="2012">
Antonietto 
<emphasis box="[668,718,366,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">et al</emphasis>
., 2012
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from the Aptian-Albian of Araripe, Pará-Maranhão and Potiguar basins, 
<collectingCountry box="[337,408,402,428]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, is highest in the anteromedian region, its posterior portion is slightly supracurvate, and it is ornamented. 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida-Lima &amp; Piovesan &amp; Sayão &amp; Lima, 2020" authorityName="Almeida-Lima &amp; Piovesan &amp; Sayão &amp; Lima" authorityYear="2020" box="[296,407,439,464]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Pattersoncypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minima" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[296,407,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">P. minima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[412,501,438,464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[412,501,438,464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="(Krommelbein &amp; Weber, 1971)" baseAuthorityName="Krommelbein &amp; Weber" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[645,1139,438,464]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Pattersoncypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salitrensis">
<emphasis box="[645,786,438,464]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">P. salitrensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Krommelbein, K. &amp; Weber, R." box="[799,1130,438,464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" pagination="1 - 93" refId="ref5038" refString="Krommelbein, K. &amp; Weber, R. (1971) Ostracoden des &quot; Nordost-Brasilianischen Wealden &quot;. Geologisches Jahrbuch, 115, 1 - 93." type="journal article" year="1971">Krömmelbein &amp; Weber, 1971</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
recorded in Aptian-Albian of Araripe and São Luís-Grajaú basins, 
<collectingCountry box="[603,674,474,500]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, by the absence of the dorsal pronounced hump. Additionally, in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Krommelbein &amp; Weber" baseAuthorityYear="1971" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Pattersoncypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salitrensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">P. salitrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the greatest width is positioned at the postero-median region and presents a more subtriangular outline in lateral view, when compared with the new species presented here. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Krommelbein &amp; Weber, 1971)" baseAuthorityName="Krommelbein &amp; Weber" baseAuthorityYear="1971" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Pattersoncypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinuata">
<emphasis box="[887,1153,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">Pattersoncypris sinuata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Krommelbein, K. &amp; Weber, R." pageId="5" pageNumber="176" pagination="1 - 93" refId="ref5038" refString="Krommelbein, K. &amp; Weber, R. (1971) Ostracoden des &quot; Nordost-Brasilianischen Wealden &quot;. Geologisches Jahrbuch, 115, 1 - 93." type="journal article" year="1971">Krömmelbein &amp; Weber, 1971</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from the Aptian-Albian of Araripe, Potiguar and Sergipe-Alagoas basins, 
<collectingCountry box="[1054,1125,582,608]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida-Lima &amp; Piovesan &amp; Sayão &amp; Lima, 2020" authorityName="Almeida-Lima &amp; Piovesan &amp; Sayão &amp; Lima" authorityYear="2020" box="[1279,1395,583,609]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Pattersoncypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minima" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1279,1296,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1311,1395,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">minima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="5" pageNumber="176" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by its dorsal hump and its bigger size. 
<taxonomicName authority="Bate, 1972" authorityName="Bate" authorityYear="1972" box="[644,1130,618,645]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Pattersoncypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micropapillosa">
<emphasis box="[644,998,618,644]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">Pattersoncypris micropapillosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bate, R. H." box="[1005,1130,618,645]" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" pagination="379 - 393" refId="ref3876" refString="Bate, R. H. (1972) Phosphatized Ostracods with Appendages from the Lower Cretaceous of Brazil. Paleontology, 15, 379 - 393." type="journal article" year="1972">Bate, 1972</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from the Aptian-Albian of Araripe, Potiguar, Cedro and Jatobá basins, 
<collectingCountry box="[658,729,654,680]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, features a pronounced dorsal hump, an equicurvate posterior margin and a typical carapace ornamentation, thus distinguishing it from 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida-Lima &amp; Piovesan &amp; Sayão &amp; Lima, 2020" authorityName="Almeida-Lima &amp; Piovesan &amp; Sayão &amp; Lima" authorityYear="2020" box="[971,1086,691,717]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Pattersoncypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minima" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[971,988,691,716]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1002,1086,691,716]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">minima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1093,1183,690,716]" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1093,1183,690,716]" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,150,752]" box="[199,1112,726,752]" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,517,726,752]" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[524,595,726,752]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, Araripe Basin, Romualdo Formation, Aptian.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
